How can I donate to the Roper Good Neighbor Fund?

The Roper Good Neighbor Fund is one of many funds held by the Foundation for LPS. All gifts can be given through their website; 95% of all donations go directly to Roper families.

Don't forget to add "Roper Good Neighbor Fund" in the fund name field.

#1

What We Do

Every year, students and families at Roper Elementary face hardships which make school, work, and home life difficult. With community support, they are able to recover and keep their families healthy and whole.

Through the Roper Good Neighbor Fund, all community members are given the opportunity to lend a helping hand to Roper Elementary staff, students, and families in crisis. It is one of many funds held by the Foundation for LPS. When other community resources fall short, this fund can be used to support Roper families facing difficult circumstances.

Ways we help Roper Rockets

  • directions_car_filled Covering car repairs so students have a safe ride to school
  • checkroom Purchasing clothes and shoes for families in emergencies
  • emoji_objects Helping with utility payments to keep families protected
  • house Paying emergency housing costs or rent in crisis situations
  • favorite Helping with other unaffordable urgent needs

#2

How to Help

The BEST way you can help your neighbors in difficult circumstances is to donate to the Roper Good Neighbor Fund through the Foundation for LPS.

Dont forget to add Roper Good Neighbor Fund in the Notes field.

Help My Neighbors

There are a number of fun ways you can contribute throughout the year:

  1. Student-led initiatives

    In 2021 Roper Ambassadors helped raise over $2000 through a school-wide coin drive.

  2. Apparel Sales

    The annual Roper PTO apparel sale often includes a unique option which goes to benefit the Good Neighbor Fund.

  3. Holiday Fundraisers

    Keep your eyes peeled during the holiday season. We offer donation opportunities like festive plant or wreath sales.

#3

Contact Us

This fund is available to all students and staff at Roper Elementary School. If you are in need of assistance, please contact Ropers student services staff member, Andrea Phillips, at:
aphilli@lps.org

If you have general questions about the Roper Good Neighbor Fund, or are looking for ways you can help raise funds for your neighbors, please fill out the contact form or email us at:
roperneighbors@gmail.com
